WikiArt (formerly known as WikiPaintings) is an online, user-editable visual art encyclopedia. Based upon a statement in its 2013 financial report, the site appears to be online since 2010. They claim to have reached 75,000 paintings as of June 2012..
As of July 2017, the site shows the following numbers:
2672 artists (156 movements in 2-level hierarchy, 253 schools/groups, 50 genres, 28 fields, 87 nationalities)
146509 artworks (160 styles, 54 genres)
Taking for example Salvador Dali, we see 1102 artworks, his creative Periods, and related artists.
As of February 2013 "the Wiki functionality of the site is still under development". The developers are based in Ukraine.
